# This empty `pages/` directory exists so Next.js does NOT mistake Vite's
# `src/pages/` for the Pages Router during migration. Next.js's auto-detector
# prefers a top-level `pages/`; finding it empty, it falls through to App Router
# (`app/`) only.
#
# Once the Vite pages are deleted (Faz 6), this whole directory can go too.
